# UI polish standards — MacTech Gear

## Mobile-first

- Test at **375px** width — no horizontal overflow
- Touch targets **≥ 44px** (buttons, nav CTA, social icons, gallery tiles)
- Full-width CTAs on small screens where appropriate

## Interactions

- Buttons and links need visible **hover** and **focus-visible** states
- No dead clicks — external links use `target="_blank"` + `rel="noopener noreferrer"`

## Consistency

- **Typography:** Barlow Condensed (headings) + DM Sans (body) — don't add random fonts
- **Colors:** use CSS variables in `:root` (`--green`, `--green-bright`, etc.)
- **Spacing:** section padding and card gaps should feel even hero → features → gallery → footer
- **Imagery:** product/outdoor tone; assets live in `assets/` with fixed filenames

## Performance

- Hero video: desktop only; poster/static image on mobile
- Don't add heavy JS libraries for a one-page site
- Prefer optimized images (PNG/JPG in `assets/images/`)

## Before calling a slice done

- [ ] Desktop and mobile look intentional, not "template"
- [ ] Hero text readable over video/image
- [ ] Gallery loads (Behold) or shows sensible fallbacks
- [ ] Shop + social links work
